Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 475 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}. Quarter @Lime{1}.

== Pico de Gallo & Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, scallions, a drizzle of oil, and juice from 1 lime wedge (2 wedges for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} with lime juice to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano, salt, and pepper; cook until just softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a third small bowl.

Add another drizzle of oil to same pan. Add @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, half the @Tex-Mex Paste{1}, half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest of each later), salt, and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Return poblano to pan; stir to combine. Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

Place a small amount of filling on one half of each @Flour Tortillas{6}. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create enchiladas. Place seam sides down in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (9-by-13-inch dish for 4 servings) or an #ovenproof pan{}.

In a #bowl{} or #liquid measuring cup{}, combine @Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce}, remaining Tex-Mex paste and Southwest Spice, and @water{1/2%cup} (3/4 cup for 4 servings).

Pour over enchiladas to thoroughly coat. Sprinkle with @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}.

Bake on top rack until sauce is bubbly and cheese has melted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Top enchiladas with lime crema and pico de gallo. Divide between plates and serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.